			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">What to do when you have a Shammy and Chanter in group?<a name="4348"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 13 03 11:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Hehe, I had a very interesting experience the other day. One that made me feel completely useless, which has never happened before. So I thought I'd share:
<br />

<br />
I was grouping with guildies, specifically, a Warrior, Pally, Cleric, Shaman, Chanter and me.  All of us were level 55 to 61, me being 55, hehe. So, we are assembling together waiting for last to show up, dealing out assignments for who does what...
<br />

<br />
I start asking my standard questions. Problem is, every answer was Shammy do this or Chanter do that. This coming from my guild leader chanter that knows her stuff.  Haste - stackable ok, slow - shammy, debuff - tash (though I could oos), buff - shammy, resists - not needed...
<br />

<br />
And so it went. I felt like a spare tire, do in a pinch if the regular ones don't work. 
<br />

<br />
Ended up that we didn't group because my chanter leader wanted to bow out and let us group, but I didn't want her to. 
<br />

<br />
It did bring up an interesting point. If you have equal level shammy, chanter and bard, who does what?  I know we can make them better, but is that all we can do in that case?
<br />

<br />
Interesting... Thoughts? No flames please, these are my friends. =)
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=547835">Maestro Sinfonian's gear... (inspect me)</a> </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
