		</table></td><td class="PanelBodyAlternate" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do when you have a Shammy and Chanter in group?<a name="4387"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 03 11:49 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been in this position many times.  There are still plenty that you can do.  You said you are currently 55, so here are some ideas, assuming you have all songs up to that point.
<br />

<br />
Cantana of Replenishment - More regen, can't have enough
<br />

<br />
Battlecry of Vah Shir - Push that haste higher
<br />

<br />
Largo's Absonant Binding - Slow won't stack, but the other debuffs are nice.  Still use it on occasion at 62. Also nice to pre-slow for other slowers.  Stuff seems to die faster stacking this slow with others.
<br />

<br />
Niv's Melody of Preservation - More health regen.  Stack Cantana and Niv's to help reduce heal casting.  I've made Clerics into nukers at times with this combo.
<br />

<br />
Chants - I recall you like to melee, but our chants damage and debuff.  Sit back and bang your drum.
<br />

<br />
Depending on what you were fighting, I most likely would of equipped my lute(7string) and sang Largo, Niv's and Cantana.  If short on dps, switch to damage.
<br />

<br />
You could also use this time to ease up on twisting to save your wrists.
<br />

<br />
Just some ideas...
<br />

<br />
Tatter D'Malion
<br />
62 bard, Sphere of Honor, Brell Serilis</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
