			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do when you have a Shammy and Chanter in group?<a name="4399"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 03 1:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>In this case, as in many cases, our job is to help other classes function better.  We arn't all that godly for melee, unless you just want to put some more out.  I would support Tatter on all his ideas.  there is ALWAYS something you can do.  Be it mana, debuffing mobs resists, snaring the mob when its incoming, lulling mobs so pulls are easier, helping with damage shield, regening, etc.
<br />

<br />
Our class is sort of unique in my eyes, wizards nuke, clerics heal, pallys do this, necros do that, blahblahblah.
<br />

<br />
The special thing about us, is you get as much out of a bard as you put in.  This can be true for other classes as well, but its where bards truely shine.  You can always tell the difference between a well-played bard and a sloppily played bard.  
<br />

<br />
just IMO.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.gaijindesign.com/lawriemalen/jedi/jedimaster.jpg" width="285" height="123" border="0"><br>:: how jedi are you? ::</a>

