			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do when you have a Shammy and Chanter in group?<a name="4419"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Feb 14 03 9:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Shammy:
<br />
Buffs (this takes a LOT of mana, but if they're not having to haste and slow they can buff a lot more fully)
<br />
Heals (no cleric?)
<br />
Canni!
<br />

<br />
Chanter:
<br />
Always let the Chanter think they're doing crowd control, and if CC is required have them do it.
<br />
Haste
<br />
Slows
<br />
KEI/Clarity
<br />

<br />
Bard:
<br />
Stackable Hastes (Ervaj and/or Vah Shir)
<br />
Group/AE regen (HP AND MP that stacks)
<br />
Niv's! (HP, AC, STR that stacks)
<br />
Debuffs (whatever you want to twist)
<br />
Rune Song (whatever you want to twist)
<br />
Further buffs (chant of battle if it stacks)
<br />
Assonance (31% slow and DoT, lasts 1 minute)
<br />
Charm (if you can sneak them in there between chanter mezzes)
<br />

<br />
There is a lot of stuff you can do. In most exp situations I find chanters are inefficient.
<br />
</span></td>
