				<td colspan="2"><span>Actually, you named my regular group. =p
<br />

<br />
Our base group is a 60 cleric, 60 warrior, 60 bard (that would be me), and a 59 chanter.
<br />

<br />
We rotate in 2 of 3 friends, a 57 shaman, a 58 ranger, and a 57 pally.
<br />

<br />
I guess part of the issue is how comfortable are you with each other?  In my group, unless the mobs are too high or just come in an enormous pack, I always do crowd control.  The chanter actually likes getting the break from it, and he plays nuker for the night along with being a buffer / debuffer.
<br />

<br />
The shaman slows better than the chanter, and the chanter hastes better than the shaman.  I throw in Warsong of the Vah Shir and Composition of Ervaj, and the blades fly.  From there, it's just a matter of what role you want to play.
<br />

<br />
You know you're playing mana battery for the night, no matter what mana buff the chanter has.  Just twist in your choice of buffs and damage and hop into the fray.  <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> 
<br />

<br />
My group loves having a chanter, bard, and shammy all at once.  =)  The mobs go down quickly and the group doesn't have any worries of loss of life, or mana.
<br />

