				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do when you have a Shammy and Chanter in group?<a name="5599"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 21 03 4:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Last 5 minutes??? What are you smokin?  Nevermind, looked over your posts, you are a level 40 twink bard, and dont even have either one of those dot, LOL.  They last just as long as fire and ice, all being 3 ticks, I know, I have them, and use them.  The only dot that last longer than 3 is the level 60 Assonance - dot/slow.  Also, ALL DS's are UNRESISTABLE, so it would make no difference which you played if you were the only one DS'ing, but psalm of warmth is a cold DS, and weakens mage DS spells, while (rarely the case) psalm of cooling cancels necro/sk self-only DS.  So for the most part, always use psalm of cooling.  Lastly, DS songs are rather pitiful, and you would do much more damage on a slowed mob (since you have a chanter/shammy slowing, point of this thread) singing another song.  Lastly, I very rarely group anywhere and have the mobs we kill take much longer than 30 seconds to kill, so dots would do very little damage before the mob is killed.  I think that some of the above posts got it right.....do what bards do best, STACK.
<br />

<br />
Stackable haste
<br />
Stackable health and mana regen
<br />
More stackable regen (Niv's)
<br />
Resists
<br />

<br />
Or if you are going for pure DPS:
<br />
Stackable Haste
<br />
Self-Haste if you have less than 34% item haste (Jonathans Whistling Warsong and Jonathan's Inspiration both stack with chanter/shammy haste)
<br />

<br />
My usual group line-up for all 8 gems is as follows:
<br />

<br />
1)haste (over the cap haste if chanter/shammy in group)
<br />
2)Hymn (I dont have epic, yet, so I use this because it doesnt require stringed)
<br />
3)Niv's for more regen
<br />
4)Snare (even if there is a druid/ranger, just in case)
<br />
5)Mez
<br />
6)Charm
<br />
7)Cantana (for downtime, between pulls, requires lute, dont play when pull is inc, as it will b-line straight to you)
<br />
8)selos (for fast get-aways)</span></td>
