				<td colspan="2"><span>My usual group included nearly everything except a bard. We run in 2 groups in mini-raid style, and are extremely effective. So, when I was looking to start the game last January, they asked me to try out a bard and see how I liked it. And I love it.
<br />

<br />
But we've got both Enchanter and Shammy, certainly, who are both great.
<br />

<br />
Still, as had been said, the glory of the bard is the ability to make things better. Vah Shir/Ervaj type haste buffs are awesome for melee types. Mana regen necessary when things get lively. Our DS stacks. Amplify our DS and even at level 50 or so it'll do 16 points of damage. Nivs is always useful.
<br />

<br />
As you climb your 50s, more and more spells will fill in slots which other classes simply cannot touch, or which stack with other classes' abilities.
<br />

<br />
In my group, I tend to have CC ready in case enchanter mana gets low, but to regularly melee and twist: Vah Shir, Nivs, and a DS. 
<br />

<br />
It's all situational, though.
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
