			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What to do when you have a Shammy and Chanter in group?<a name="7121"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 7 03 11:09 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Wow you were in a perfect group to show off your skills!!!
<br />

<br />
Song of Occlusion will have the Shammy and Enchanter thanking you profusely because they will be able to Slow and/or mes faster.  I have Requiem of Time and I occlude and slow before the mob gets to my tank.  If multiple mobs are coming I try to get in the best spot to hit em all with occlude first and then see if I can help chanter with mesing.
<br />

<br />
When you settle in on meleeing use your stackable haste songs and rune and Nivs.  Warsong and Psalm of Veeshan adds about 50 plus to DS and if you have Rizolna's Song you'll make casters in your group pleased with the big add to the damage they can do.  Druids, mages and wizzies love having a bard with Riz's a druid critical blast will do about 2400 damage with Riz's will do upwards of 3800.  
<br />

<br />
If you are fighting caster mobs and have the mana drain song it cuts down on the number AEs they can do.  If you have Elemental Chorus you can protect a large portion of your guild from the full impact of a mob's AE.  In a regular group Psalm of Veeshan or Mystic Shielding or whatever Psalm is needed will make all healers very happy.
<br />

<br />
I your down time ask the Shammy and Chanter if occlusion helped em with their resists.  It never hurts to let everyone know you were pretty busy during the fight.  Since as you know you can't always type.  Also, get feedback from em on what mobs might need special attention for debuffing from occlusion or curtailing chant.
<br />

<br />
All the other classes seem to focus in on the critical hits a tank can dish out so don't be afraid to let your group know what you did to help.  But do it in a nnice way.
<br />

<br />
Keyes Sarabande level 65 bard on Rodcet Nife with over 380 days played</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
